1
00:00:04,416 --> 00:00:05,849
Hey, it's been a while.

2
00:00:06,083 --> 00:00:09,066
By the way, thank you new and returning viewers

3
00:00:09,066 --> 00:00:11,033
for checking out my previous CachyOS video

4
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:12,233
and having a talk with me.

5
00:00:12,233 --> 00:00:13,666
It was pretty relaxing.

6
00:00:13,666 --> 00:00:15,099
So let's get to the topic.

7
00:00:15,099 --> 00:00:17,199
Where was I in the past few months?

8
00:00:17,466 --> 00:00:19,833
You see, to new viewers, you might not know much.

9
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:21,266
So I'm gonna get you up to speed.

10
00:00:21,266 --> 00:00:23,800
I called a hiatus for my regular game streams

11
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:26,633
to restructure my stream content.

12
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:28,566
With personal expectations that

13
00:00:28,566 --> 00:00:30,783
I'll still regularly release videos,

14
00:00:30,783 --> 00:00:32,500
but the videos have not been out.

15
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:33,816
What happened during it?

16
00:00:33,816 --> 00:00:37,366
In the first month of a hiatus, which was December of 2025,

17
00:00:37,366 --> 00:00:39,750
I began working on sorting out my messy setup

18
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:41,450
in my Unraid NAS server,

19
00:00:41,450 --> 00:00:42,649
 which is a mess.

20
00:00:42,649 --> 00:00:45,183
If you are not one to regularly keep things tidy,

21
00:00:45,183 --> 00:00:48,200
have a look at your desktop and you tell me what you see.

22
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,783
Yeah...

23
00:00:49,783 --> 00:00:50,883
That's what I meant.

24
00:00:50,883 --> 00:00:53,100
But at a larger scale that came biting back at me

25
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:54,816
at my workflow efficiency.

26
00:00:54,816 --> 00:00:55,933
Towards the end of December,

27
00:00:55,933 --> 00:00:58,783
I realized I needed far more time than usual.

28
00:00:58,783 --> 00:01:01,183
So I began laying out things that I needed to work on.

29
00:01:01,183 --> 00:01:04,349
Which is a few sets of parts that you saw in the Trello post

30
00:01:04,349 --> 00:01:06,883
 that I recently put up in YouTube community post.

31
00:01:06,883 --> 00:01:08,150
I had seen the sheer horrors

32
00:01:08,150 --> 00:01:09,750
of the things I had to work on.

33
00:01:09,750 --> 00:01:12,950
I gotta lock the heck in.

34
00:01:12,950 --> 00:01:13,683
Fast forward.

35
00:01:13,683 --> 00:01:14,633
New Years happened.

36
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:16,083
Fireworks popping everywhere.

37
00:01:16,083 --> 00:01:18,500
I took a breather and prayed,

38
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:22,366
Everything's gotta go smoothly to plan.

39
00:01:22,366 --> 00:01:23,766
Until it didn't.

40
00:01:23,766 --> 00:01:26,700
My relative got hit by a vehicle and was admitted to hospital.

41
00:01:27,066 --> 00:01:29,533
They lived alone, so after they discharged,

42
00:01:29,533 --> 00:01:31,466
they had to stay over at my place

43
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:34,666
because my family was the only reachable and closest relative.

44
00:01:34,666 --> 00:01:35,950
But this is Asia.

45
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:37,583
We don't have an abundance of rooms.

46
00:01:37,583 --> 00:01:40,400
So in times of emergency, we let them live in my studio room

47
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:43,166
I've recorded and worked in all these times.

48
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:44,966
Thinking it's going to be a few weeks thing,

49
00:01:44,966 --> 00:01:46,816
I just moved a small amount of my stuff.

50
00:01:47,133 --> 00:01:50,266
Namely my mic, my mouse, my Steam Deck

51
00:01:50,266 --> 00:01:53,033
over so I can continue working on server stuff.

52
00:01:53,033 --> 00:01:56,700
Only to learn that we're living in the AI bubble.

53
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:58,816
The laptop I used to work on stuff,

54
00:01:58,816 --> 00:02:00,816
remember that CachyOS laptop?

55
00:02:00,816 --> 00:02:05,250
began terminating my active programs and I realized one thing.

56
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:09,016
I'm out of RAM for the work that I was doing.

57
00:02:09,016 --> 00:02:12,633
In a miniature panic, I quickly get RustDesk functional and working,

58
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:14,433
which thankfully, did.

59
00:02:14,433 --> 00:02:15,366
Crisis averted.

60
00:02:15,366 --> 00:02:18,566
I can work on lighter stuff that needs more browser tabs.

61
00:02:18,566 --> 00:02:21,533
As time passes and a couple of revisits into my studio room

62
00:02:21,533 --> 00:02:24,750
to check on stuff, I sense a suspicious smell.

63
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:27,949
In secret, I had a chat with my mom on what's going on,

64
00:02:27,949 --> 00:02:29,533
and my mom seems to agree with me.

65
00:02:29,533 --> 00:02:30,966
There's a hint of tobacco

66
00:02:30,966 --> 00:02:33,983
in the smell of my entire studio room.

67
00:02:33,983 --> 00:02:36,716
So for a few days, we've monitored the situation

68
00:02:36,716 --> 00:02:38,883
and been secretly observing what my relative's

69
00:02:38,883 --> 00:02:40,633
been doing behind our backs.

70
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:43,133
With clear and concrete evidence,

71
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:44,849
we've came to the conclusion that

72
00:02:44,849 --> 00:02:46,750
they smoke in my studio room

73
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:48,500
with no airflow.

74
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:51,166
I remember vividly that my mom had made clear to them

75
00:02:51,166 --> 00:02:54,250
that we had a no smoking policy in this entire house,

76
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:56,183
but they've broken that one rule.

77
00:02:56,183 --> 00:02:57,783
My respect for this said relative

78
00:02:57,783 --> 00:03:00,033
is shattering right before my eyes.

79
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:00,983
(Sigh)

80
00:03:00,983 --> 00:03:03,966
During my personal research, I found that third-hand smoking

81
00:03:03,966 --> 00:03:06,150
can cause problems to anyone who comes into contact

82
00:03:06,150 --> 00:03:08,400
with objects that nicotine touches,

83
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:11,166
which stays for an extremely long time.

84
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:13,349
Now if you know any content creator, or heck,

85
00:03:13,349 --> 00:03:14,733
even just an average gamer,

86
00:03:14,733 --> 00:03:16,316
you know how difficult it is

87
00:03:16,316 --> 00:03:19,666
to take down an entire setup to clean every surface

88
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:21,133
that the nicotine touched,

89
00:03:21,133 --> 00:03:23,800
let alone getting baking soda, vinegar,

90
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:27,983
or worse, trisodium phosphate, and clean every surface.

91
00:03:27,983 --> 00:03:29,816
Knowing that they had smoke in my studio room

92
00:03:29,816 --> 00:03:31,383
and in the bathroom attached to it,

93
00:03:31,383 --> 00:03:34,183
the idea of needing to clean any speck of nicotine

94
00:03:34,183 --> 00:03:36,900
off of every visible surface

95
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:39,050
is going to set me back a month or two,

96
00:03:39,050 --> 00:03:41,116
heck, even three more months.

97
00:03:41,116 --> 00:03:44,216
And that's on top of what few months I projected needing

98
00:03:44,216 --> 00:03:47,449
for my background restructuring I was initially working on.

99
00:03:47,449 --> 00:03:49,849
After a few hours, I calmed down,

100
00:03:49,849 --> 00:03:51,783
figured I might have overreacted,

101
00:03:51,783 --> 00:03:54,750
but things gone way worse days after.

102
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:57,966
In the midst of my occasional internal rage against them,

103
00:03:57,966 --> 00:03:58,949
backup came.

104
00:03:58,949 --> 00:04:01,949
A distant relative family came over to visit him,

105
00:04:01,949 --> 00:04:05,833
and my mom had a plan to quietly confiscate their cigarettes

106
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:08,316
and hand it off to the relative for removal.

107
00:04:08,316 --> 00:04:10,883
And hand it off to the relative for removal.

108
00:04:10,883 --> 00:04:12,366
At the end of the reunion,

109
00:04:12,366 --> 00:04:14,583
they planned to confront them directly.

110
00:04:14,583 --> 00:04:17,283
During the confrontation, they flat out denied

111
00:04:17,283 --> 00:04:18,383
that they have smoked,

112
00:04:18,383 --> 00:04:20,783
and was perplexed that we knew there was one cig missing

113
00:04:20,783 --> 00:04:22,116
from the first time we checked.

114
00:04:22,116 --> 00:04:24,949
To some of y'all who think it's an invasion of privacy,

115
00:04:24,949 --> 00:04:26,133
screw y'all!

116
00:04:26,133 --> 00:04:27,199
I own this damn house

117
00:04:27,199 --> 00:04:31,266
and I made the smoking policy pretty dang clear.

118
00:04:31,266 --> 00:04:32,683
Well, technically my mom.

119
00:04:32,683 --> 00:04:34,666
And I'm acting within my right to know

120
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:36,616
if they've smoked in my premise.

121
00:04:36,616 --> 00:04:38,333
With those specific reactions,

122
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:41,083
all trust I had on them had been lost.

123
00:04:41,083 --> 00:04:42,733
I thought of giving them a little chance

124
00:04:42,733 --> 00:04:45,616
considering there should be no cigs anymore.

125
00:04:45,616 --> 00:04:47,116
Right?

126
00:04:47,616 --> 00:04:48,483
Right?

127
00:04:48,483 --> 00:04:49,783
Until days later.

128
00:04:49,783 --> 00:04:51,783
I spotted something sitting on the pile of

129
00:04:51,783 --> 00:04:54,283
personal valuable belongings of theirs.

130
00:04:54,283 --> 00:04:55,833
An e-cigarette.

131
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:59,083
Knowing I'm gonna have a fit and that'll be bad,

132
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:01,033
I quickly relayed it to my mom,

133
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:03,750
and closed myself in the bedroom that I've been working on

134
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:06,800
and just focused on working on the NAS.

135
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,733
Within a day, I learned from her that

136
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:11,483
she has confiscated the e-cig quietly too.

137
00:05:11,483 --> 00:05:14,533
Pair that with their surprised reaction to the fact that it's missing.

138
00:05:14,533 --> 00:05:17,183
Of course they have no guts to ask us about it,

139
00:05:17,183 --> 00:05:19,850
because that'll mean they'll admit that the cig was theirs.

140
00:05:19,850 --> 00:05:21,649
It's been a month since the incident,

141
00:05:21,649 --> 00:05:24,066
and things seem to have stabilized.

142
00:05:24,066 --> 00:05:26,916
Another thing that has been eating me silently.

143
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:27,949
Burnouts.

144
00:05:27,949 --> 00:05:30,250
You see, when I was moving into this new place,

145
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:32,066
I got myself two rooms out of the few

146
00:05:32,066 --> 00:05:33,933
in the apartment that we bought.

147
00:05:33,933 --> 00:05:37,466
Just so I could solve this long-standing psychological issue 

148
00:05:37,466 --> 00:05:41,766
of having the work and play in one single room at my old place.

149
00:05:41,766 --> 00:05:43,800
By separating work and non-work,

150
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:47,716
I felt a nice release from what feels like eternal work.

151
00:05:47,716 --> 00:05:50,066
If I see my work table right when I wake up...

152
00:05:50,066 --> 00:05:52,433
Ugh, that ain't a good feeling.

153
00:05:52,433 --> 00:05:55,383
But with my laptop sitting just across my bedroom,

154
00:05:55,383 --> 00:05:58,266
it's starting to feel a lot like my old place again.

155
00:05:58,266 --> 00:06:01,550
Pair that to the fact that I've gotten used to a three-monitor setup,

156
00:06:01,550 --> 00:06:03,366
I had at maximum: two,

157
00:06:03,366 --> 00:06:04,516
or at minimum: one.

158
00:06:04,516 --> 00:06:08,033
Instead, these early few weeks had been my most

159
00:06:08,033 --> 00:06:10,466
unproductive weeks in my lifetime,

160
00:06:10,466 --> 00:06:12,883
with barely any motivation working at all.

161
00:06:12,883 --> 00:06:14,683
I was also at my all-time low.

162
00:06:14,683 --> 00:06:16,183
Fast forward to a few weeks after that,

163
00:06:16,183 --> 00:06:18,383
my relative offered to take them in

164
00:06:18,383 --> 00:06:21,283
for periods where the recheckup date gap

165
00:06:21,283 --> 00:06:23,399
spans further than a few days.

166
00:06:23,399 --> 00:06:25,149
So we took up on that offer.

167
00:06:25,149 --> 00:06:27,766
After a few weeks, they were cleared to work

168
00:06:27,766 --> 00:06:30,566
and discharged, and is back to their own place.

169
00:06:30,566 --> 00:06:31,633
Thankfully.

170
00:06:31,633 --> 00:06:34,750
Now, with you being able to watch this video in itself is a blessing, 

171
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:36,850
because as of the time I published this video,

172
00:06:36,850 --> 00:06:40,616
my entire setup had been torn down thoroughly, cleaned thoroughly,

173
00:06:40,616 --> 00:06:44,149
and the NAS is somewhat sorted, but is still a mess.

174
00:06:44,149 --> 00:06:46,850
I might have to redo that, if it's necessary.

175
00:06:46,850 --> 00:06:49,466
Now, I hope to get back to the groove of content creation,

176
00:06:49,466 --> 00:06:51,133
but we'll see what happens first.

177
00:06:51,133 --> 00:06:52,783
Now, with that long story out of the way,

178
00:06:52,783 --> 00:06:53,949
 I'd like to cap it off with:

179
00:06:53,949 --> 00:06:57,050
I greatly appreciate y'all sticking around with me.

180
00:06:57,050 --> 00:06:58,833
Despite my silence at times,

181
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:01,899
and constantly looking forward to my content regardless,

182
00:07:01,899 --> 00:07:05,283
it's been a crazy rough start of 2026 for me.

183
00:07:05,283 --> 00:07:06,649
But I hope it gets better from here.

184
00:07:06,649 --> 00:07:09,683
While I can't promise a date of return, from what I'm seeing,

185
00:07:09,683 --> 00:07:14,016
I predict I might return probably around May or so.

186
00:07:14,016 --> 00:07:16,283
It's just speculation, but there will be a new video

187
00:07:16,283 --> 00:07:19,050
when I can confirm that I can continue working comfortably.

188
00:07:19,050 --> 00:07:20,566
There might be a stream around then.

189
00:07:20,566 --> 00:07:23,250
With that said, thank you so much for your patience.

190
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:24,250
And once again,

191
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:25,483
OtsuMelo deshita (It's been ya girl Mel).

192
00:07:25,483 --> 00:07:26,083
Peace.

